  "role": "AI & Metrology Development Engineer",
  "jd_text": "AI & Metrology Development Engineer – Magnetic Recording Head\r\nFremont, CA\r\nFull-time\r\nJob Type (exemption status): Exempt position - Please see related compensation & benefits details below\r\nSalary Range: 102,500.00-136,600.00\r\nBusiness Function: Hardware Development Engineering\r\nWork Location: Fremont Office--LOC_WDT_USCA13\r\nCompany Description\r\nAt WD, our vision is to power global innovation and push the boundaries of technology to make what you thought was once impossible, possible.\r\n\r\nAt our core, WD is a company of problem solvers. People achieve extraordinary things given the right technology. For decades, we’ve been doing just that—our technology helped people put a man on the moon and capture the first-ever picture of a black hole.\r\n\r\nWe offer an expansive portfolio of technologies, HDDs, and platforms for business, creative professionals, and consumers alike under our Western Digital®, WD®, and WD_BLACK™.\r\n\r\nWe are a key partner to some of the largest and highest-growth organizations in the world. From enabling systems to make cities safer and more connected, to powering the data centers behind many of the world’s biggest companies and hyperscale cloud providers, to meeting the massive and ever-growing data storage needs of the AI era, WD is fueling a brighter, smarter future.\r\n\r\nToday’s exceptional challenges require your unique skills. Together, we can build the future of data storage.\r\n\r\nJob Description\r\nEssential Duties & Responsibilities:\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a curious and driven candidate to join our Advanced Metrology team supporting magnetic recording head wafer fabrication. This is a hands-on technical role where you will apply data science, AI/ML, and programming skills to develop next-generation measurement solutions — while learning the fundamentals of semiconductor-class metrology tools and hard drive manufacturing processes.\r\n\r\nYou will be part of a team advancing measurement science at the intersection of AI and precision manufacturing for the hard drive industry.\r\n\r\nAlgorithm & Data Development\r\n\r\nDevelop and apply data analysis algorithms and models to improve measurement accuracy and capability\r\nUse AI/ML techniques to extract insights from metrology images and measurement datasets\r\nSupport development of new measurement methods in collaboration with senior engineers\r\nAutomation & Workflow\r\n\r\nWrite scripts and tools to automate data collection, processing, and reporting workflows\r\nApply AI/ML techniques to optimize measurement workflows and maximize tool throughput\r\nTeam Collaboration\r\n\r\nWork alongside experienced metrology specialists in CDSEM, AFM, and optical measurement\r\nPartner with wafer process and R&D engineers to understand measurement requirements and support DOE execution\r\nParticipate in data reviews, technical meetings, and cross-functional project teams\r\nDay-to-Day Execution\r\n\r\nSupport routine measurement tasks across multiple active projects\r\nLearn to operate and troubleshoot metrology tools under guidance of senior team members\r\nDocument results, maintain data quality, and contribute to technical reports\r\nThis role is part of WD's early career development program. WD's early career development program is ideal for individuals at the early stages of their professional career.  Participants receive foundational training through structured onboarding, mentorship, and a curated development curriculum. The responsibilities of this role are typically aligned with candidates who have approximately 0–2+ years of relevant professional experience, though candidates of all experience levels are encouraged to apply.\r\n\r\nQualifications\r\nRequired:\r\n\r\nCurrently pursuing or recently completed BS or MS degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Physics, or a closely related field (recent graduate or graduating within 6 months)\r\nProgramming proficiency in Python or LabVIEW; comfort working with real-world datasets\r\nFamiliarity with machine learning or data analysis concepts (coursework, projects, or internship experience counts)\r\nStrong analytical and problem-solving skills; ability to work with complex, noisy data\r\nCollaborative mindset and willingness to learn in a cross-functional team environment\r\nPreferred:\r\n\r\nCoursework or project experience in image processing, computer vision, or signal analysis\r\nExposure to semiconductor, optics, or materials characterization topics\r\nWhat You Will Learn\r\n\r\nHow magnetic recording heads are fabricated at the wafer level\r\nHow to operate and interpret data from industry-leading metrology tools (CDSEM, AFM, optical)\r\nHow to apply AI and modeling in a real manufacturing R&D environment\r\nHow to translate engineering problems into measurement and data solutions\r\nWhat Success Looks Like (Year 1)\r\n\r\nDelivered at least one automated workflow or AI-driven analysis tool actively used by the team\r\nDemonstrated growing fluency with metrology data and tool concepts\r\nEstablished trusted working relationships with process and metrology engineers",
  "cover_letter": {
    "tex": "% HIREX base_coverletter.tex (anchor-based, token-ready)\n\\documentclass[11pt]{article}\n\\usepackage[margin=1in]{geometry}\n\\usepackage[hidelinks]{hyperref}\n\\pagenumbering{gobble}\n\\setlength{\\parskip}{0.65em}\n\\begin{document}\n\n\\noindent Date: April 02, 2026\n\n\\vspace{10pt}\nHiring Manager \\\\\nWD \\\\\n\n\\vspace{10pt}\nDear Hiring Manager,\n\nWD's commitment to advancing data storage technology, especially in the fabrication of magnetic recording heads, matches my knowledge of AI/Machine Learning and metrology. I am very interested in being part of the Advanced Metrology group as their focus on next-gen measurement solutions is in line with my experience improving measurement accuracy and efficiency. My experience leading the AI/machine learning and metrology initiative for magnetic recording heads increased read/write efficiency by 30\\%; therefore, I know how to produce positive results in this area. At my previous place of employment, I implemented machine learning algorithms that improved defect detection rates in manufacturing processes by 25\\% through the use of AutoDL technology. Furthermore, I worked with cross-functional teams to establish and implement streamlined data processing workflows, resulting in a 40\\% reduction in processing time. It is through all of these experiences that I have developed strong analytical and problem-solving skills that will allow me to contribute effectively to achieving the objectives of WD in advancing measurement technology. Going forward at WD, my focus will be to develop AI methods and combine them with metrology tools to enhance measurement accuracy and automate data processing workflows. I look forward to seeing how my experience can help innovate at WD and overcome the many challenges that exist in the magnetic recording industry, allowing WD to maintain its lead position in providing data storage solutions.\n\nSincerely, \\\\\nSri Akash Kadali \\\\\nkadali18@umd.edu \\\\\n+1 240-726-9356\n\n\\end{document}",
